<item>
            <title>[LU-15923] ll_dir_ioctl():function puts 1128 bytes on stack</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15923</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Oleg, it looks like the Misc Code Checks Robot is reporting an error in the commit messsage of every patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Misc Code Checks Robot (Gatekeeper helper)
If you believe the warnings are incorrect, please leave a comment with your explanations as a reply to the warning.

Line 1:  lustre/llite/dir.c:
 warn: ll_dir_ioctl():function puts 1128 bytes on stack
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I ran &quot;&lt;tt&gt;make checkstack&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on el7.9 and el8.5 and it didn&apos;t show this much stack usage, only about 512 bytes, and I didn&apos;t see any large structures being declared.  Could this be caused by aggressive inline of functions being called?  Outside of krb5 functions, the major users are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;544 lustre:ll_lookup_it
528 ptlrpc_gss:rsc_parse
512 lustre:ll_dir_ioctl
352 osc:osc_page_print
336 mgc:mgc_apply_recover_logs
312 ptlrpc:_debug_req
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
